<subSubSection id="C333655AFFACFF85BA97578C653E11E9" box="[199,1339,1221,1246]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9636D1FFACFF85BA97578C653E11E9" blockId="3.[151,1437,1077,1642]" box="[199,1339,1221,1246]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
<emphasis id="B95DEAC3FFACFF85BA97578C612F11E9" bold="true" box="[199,298,1221,1246]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Habitat.</emphasis>
Marine, intertidal; coarse sand, 
<quantity id="4CD19B34FFACFF85B8C3578C630711EA" box="[659,770,1221,1246]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" unit="cm" value="17.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="15.0">15–20 cm</quantity>
below surface, between low and mid-water levels.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C333655AFFACFF85BA9757A063D5107D" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9636D1FFACFF85BA9757A063D5107D" blockId="3.[151,1437,1077,1642]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
<emphasis id="B95DEAC3FFACFF85BA9757A061651035" bold="true" box="[199,352,1257,1282]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Distribution.</emphasis>
Widespread, recorded from numerous areas and localities outside the 
<typeStatus id="54928873FFACFF85BED057A364B51035" box="[1152,1200,1258,1282]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">type</typeStatus>
locality (off palazzo Donn’Anna, Naples, 
<collectingCountry id="F33E7641FFACFF85BBD9564461BB1011" box="[393,446,1293,1318]" name="Italy" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Italy</collectingCountry>
) including the West and East Mediterranean Sea, Northern Europe, British Isles, 
<collectingCountry id="F33E7641FFACFF85BF34564765991011" box="[1380,1436,1294,1318]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">USA</collectingCountry>
(Atlantic, Gulf coasts and 
<collectingRegion id="49EDF833FFACFF85BBEE5678620A107D" box="[446,527,1329,1354]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Florida</collectingRegion>
Keys) and 
<collectingCountry id="F33E7641FFACFF85B8DF567862EE107D" box="[655,747,1329,1354]" name="Somalia" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Somalia</collectingCountry>
(as 
<emphasis id="B95DEAC3FFACFF85B949567B633D107E" box="[793,824,1330,1353]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">M.</emphasis>
cf 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D52FFACFF85B90B567863C5107D" authorityName="Remane" authorityYear="1927" box="[859,960,1329,1354]" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Macrodasyidae" genus="Macrodasys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="caudatus">
<emphasis id="B95DEAC3FFACFF85B90B567863C5107D" box="[859,960,1329,1354]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">caudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C333655AFFACFF85BA97561C63A7135D" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9636D1FFACFF85BA97561C63A7135D" blockId="3.[151,1437,1077,1642]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
<emphasis id="B95DEAC3FFACFF85BA97561C613E1059" bold="true" box="[199,315,1365,1390]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to the literature, the species appears to be eurytopic, having been found in fine to coarse sand, mostly with detritus or mud, but also in 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D52FFACFF85B8C65630631610A5" authorityName="Yarrell" authorityYear="1836" box="[662,787,1401,1426]" class="Leptocardii" family="Branchiostomatidae" genus="Amphioxus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphioxiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95DEAC3FFACFF85B8C65630631610A5" box="[662,787,1401,1426]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Amphioxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sand and among algae (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB84B20FFACFF85BE075630652010A5" author="Todaro, M. A. &amp; Balsamo, M. &amp; Tongiorgi, P." box="[1111,1317,1401,1426]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" pagination="471 - 485" refId="ref10633" refString="Todaro, M. A., Balsamo, M. &amp; Tongiorgi, P. (1992) Marine gastrotrichs from the Tuscan Archipelago (Tyrrhenian Sea): I. Macrodasyida, with description of three new species, Bollettino di Zoologia, 59, 471 - 485. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 11250009209386709" type="journal article" year="1992">
Todaro 
<emphasis id="B95DEAC3FFACFF85BEFC563364D810A5" box="[1196,1245,1401,1426]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">et al</emphasis>
. 1992
</bibRefCitation>
).The wide distribution and the variety of habitats call for a better comparison of the geographic populations; future comparisons should include molecular data. According to W.D. Hummon (personal communication to MAT), the records of 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D52FFACFF85BB4456AF61A710C9" authorityName="Remane" authorityYear="1927" box="[276,418,1509,1534]" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Macrodasyidae" genus="Macrodasys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="caudatus">
<emphasis id="B95DEAC3FFACFF85BB4456AF61A710C9" box="[276,418,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">M. caudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry id="F33E7641FFACFF85B84956AF625410C9" box="[537,593,1510,1534]" name="United States of America" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">USA</collectingCountry>
actually should be considered records of 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D52FFACFF85BE6756AF659210C9" authority="Evans, 1994" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1994" box="[1079,1431,1509,1534]" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Macrodasyidae" genus="Macrodasys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="meristocytalis">
<emphasis id="B95DEAC3FFACFF85BE6756AF644B10CA" box="[1079,1102,1510,1533]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95DEAC3FFACFF85BE3056AC64F810C9" box="[1120,1277,1509,1534]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">meristocytalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB84B20FFACFF85BF5756AF659210C9" author="Evans, W. A." box="[1287,1431,1510,1534]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" pagination="239 - 255" refId="ref8292" refString="Evans, W. A. (1994) Morphological variability in warm-temperate and subtropical populations of Macrodasys (Gastrotricha: Macrodasyida: Macrodasyidae) with description of seven new species. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 107, 239 - 255." type="journal article" year="1994">Evans, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; similarly, the Indian record from Kerala beaches is most unlikely to be 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D52FFACFF85B9E55543643A1315" authorityName="Remane" authorityYear="1927" box="[949,1087,1545,1570]" class="Gastrotricha (awaiting allocation)" family="Macrodasyidae" genus="Macrodasys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Macrodasyida" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" phylum="Gastrotricha" rank="species" species="caudatus">
<emphasis id="B95DEAC3FFACFF85B9E55543643A1315" box="[949,1087,1545,1570]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">M. caudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, due to the lack of information regarding the shape and size of the accessory sexual organs (i.e., caudal- and frontal organ). It is evident that new material is needed to perform a robust identification of these animals.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
